## Quick Reference

### Project Tech Stack
- **Framework**: React 18.2.0
- **Routing**: React Router DOM 7.9.6
- **UI Library**: React Bootstrap 2.10.10, Bootstrap 5.3.8
- **Build Tool**: Vite 5.0.8
- **Styling**: CSS files per component + Bootstrap classes
- **File Extensions**: All JSX files use `.jsx` extension (required for Vite)

### Key Architecture Decisions
- Functional components only (no class components)
- Component-based CSS architecture (one CSS file per component)
- localStorage for persistence (demo mode - prepare for API)
- React Router for navigation
- Bootstrap for responsive layout

### File Organization
```
src/
  ├── components/     # Reusable components (Header.jsx, Footer.jsx, etc.)
  ├── pages/         # Page-level components (Home.jsx, etc.)
  ├── assets/        # Static assets (images, etc.)
  ├── App.jsx        # Main app component with routes
  └── main.jsx       # Entry point (Vite)
```

