## Common Tasks Checklist

When creating a new component:
- [ ] Use functional component with hooks
- [ ] Use `.jsx` extension for all JSX files (required for Vite)
- [ ] Create matching CSS file (ComponentName.css)
- [ ] Follow import order (React → Router → Third-party → Components → Assets → CSS)
- [ ] Include `.jsx` extension in all component imports
- [ ] Use PascalCase for file and component name
- [ ] Export as default export
- [ ] Include proper PropTypes or TypeScript types (when implemented)

When adding navigation:
- [ ] Use `useNavigate()` hook
- [ ] Use `Link` for internal links
- [ ] Add route to `App.jsx`
- [ ] Test navigation flow

When managing state:
- [ ] Use `useState` for local state
- [ ] Use `useEffect` for side effects
- [ ] Clean up effects (event listeners, intervals)
- [ ] Use `localStorage` for persistence (demo mode)

